Everything is viewed through the prism of US-China rivalry. The US has invested in AI like there’s no tomorrow or rather as if AGI will arrive next year. China has so far invested pretty modestly. Now that they’ve caught up with the frontier will they also invest aggressively? https://t.co/akhoD3baFP

@Midnight_Captl What’s your basis for that assertion/

I think the gap has always been roughly 6-9 months? I don’t remember it ever being 6-7 weeks. In any event, I think the point is that they are keeping up with the frontier with a persistent lag. And that’s likely enough to encourage China to go into a big spending spree. The Claude models aren’t exactly great at image gen either.

@Midnight_Captl It remains to be seen if the anti-distillation measures work or if the Chinese AI labs require distillation to keep up

@tulipking this is one of the most accurate takes on all of X regarding the Saylor situation right now

@tulipking i think there’s structurally a ton of hidden weakness in BTCUSD that people haven’t noticed yet because saylor is doing his absolute best to hide it. but the sharks smell blood and i don’t know how long he can keep doing this

@tulipking CT will give me shit for a while for the 400k call and that’s well deserved, but the thing is my thesis remained consistent. he tried to crime it and it failed. guess what’s next

@tulipking i said end of the year i didn’t say which one

@LeeorShimron @tulipking rookie mistake to compare trading volume to a guy who’s 100% price insensitive and just blasts at any price to take supply off the market forever

@LottoLabs not sure why this matters

ok you won’t be the first person to install gemma 8 on your refrigerator so what

when it gets to that point it’ll only take 1-2 months for user friendly options to become available

until then they can use claude

@ciruai @LottoLabs i’ve been an expert in this game for 10 years i’m not going anywhere

@LogikaAgency @alightinastorm most gamers don’t care about that at all, i don’t think it’s remotely the most important question. even UE6 isn’t focused on graphic fidelity anymore

the fact that people expect a billion dollar budget on gta6 is a liability to rockstar, not an asset

i’m going to go out on a limb and call that gta6 is the last major gta game. they’re gonna try to turn it into “roblox for adults”, with all kinds of games inside the platform. if they succeed, they won’t want to risk it all with gta7. if they don’t succeed, they won’t want to spend a decade working on another one

as for industrial design, i don’t know much about that, i can imagine that UE will hold some advantages there. the economics are very different

@alightinastorm @LogikaAgency yeah exactly. interestingly the roblox engine is fairly capable graphically considering how scalable it is (it can run on actual potatoes). but most games don’t use those capabilities at all because it’s not what most gamers want

